I asked the cashier if I could have those items and he said okay.  He came back with 2 ketchup  for large fries, 1 cup of blue that was small for 20 WINGS and few tissue.  I asked him if I could get another one because I have 20 wings and all other place give at least two for that many wings.   He said "sure 50 cent more".   I'm like wow no that's okay .  I won't go here anymore thats crazy I understand if I had to and asked for two more I get it but one for 20 wings come on.

Checkers is on the list of one of the good tasting foods that is horrible for u. But if you are looking for food that hits your taste buds..then Checkers is it. If you are looking for anything healthy then I'd stay far away from here. I would also add My opinion is only based off the items i usually buy. I have not tried everything off the menu..actually I've only had about 5% of items off the menu. The burgers are pretty good. I actually like their burgers more than other fast food chains (except 5guys and shake shack). The fries are amazing! And are seasoned. The mozzarella sticks are also pretty good. Now my "go to" food whenever i go to checkers is the honey garlic bbq boneless wings! Mouth watering..sweet with a lil spice kick to it. Honestly if they ever stopped selling it i might not go back to checkers. I noticed the price may vary depending on location. The Checkers in Harlem charge 2.99 for 5 wings..and there was 2 in the Bronx that were charging 3.99. I normally order a 10piece for about 6.53. Now the catch is if you like dipping sauce they do charge..which im not a fan of. I also noticed that they will not give you a plastic bag unless you ask. With them saucy wings i recommend getting a plastic bag because the sauce can leak through the paper bag and rip (i found out the hard way one day).
